Dehydrated can be ran automatically using a SystemD unit file and a timer.
Please customize the following file as needed.

Timer file, usually deployed as /etc/systemd/system/dehydrated.timer

---
[Unit]
Description=Run dehydrated certificate refresh

[Timer]
OnCalendar=Mon 13:00

[Install]
WantedBy=timers.target
---

Unit file, usually deployed as /etc/systemd/system/dehydrated.service
The unit file provides basic sandboxing.
---
[Unit]
Description=Run dehydrated certificate refresh

[Service]
Type=oneshot
ProtectSystem=strict
ProtectHome=yes
ReadWritePaths=/var/lib/dehydrated
PrivateTmp=yes
ExecStart=/usr/bin/dehydrated --cron

# You can execute commands after dehydrated to deploy the certificates
# ExecStartPost=+/bin/systemctl reload nginx.service
---
